title: Venezuelan Political Prisoners Reunite With Family After Release | 10 News
description: Venezuela freed several prominent opposition figures from prison on Sunday, a month after the government announced a new series of releases.  María Corina Machado’s lawyer Perkins Rocha and opposition politician Juan Pablo Guanipa were released in an effort to continue complying with US demands to free political prisoners.  There were emotional scenes in Valencia as two leaders of the Vente Venezuela party, from Nobel Peace Prize laureate Maria Corina Machado's movement, were released, along with a former city councillor.
